ExecDesc.value: Samba WINS Server Name Registration Handling Stack Buffer Overflow (IPv6 Version)

EngDesc.value: A stack-based buffer overflow vulnerability exists in the way Samba handles WINS messages. The vulnerability is due to a boundary error while sending NetBIOS replies. Remote attackers can exploit this vulnerability by sending a specially crafted WINS messages to the Samba WINS interface. Successful exploitation of this vulnerability allows attackers to execute arbitrary code on the vulnerable system in the context of the affected process. (IPv6 Version)
